text: Pavlovo-Posadsky District () is an administrativeLaw #11/2013-OZ and municipalLaw #41/2005-OZ district (raion), one of the thirty-six in Moscow Oblast, Russia. It is located in the east of the oblast. The area of the district is . Its administrative center is the town of Pavlovsky Posad. Population: 83,520 (2010 Census); The population of Pavlovsky Posad accounts for 76.3% of the district's total population. ==References== ===Notes=== ===Sources=== * * * Category:Districts of Moscow Oblast __NOTOC__
